Thai and Sushi place. Many variety. It includes the Thai food. This sushi place look like Thai chef prepares the sushi. They are well train for their sushi preparation. The place is big with a lot of seat including the bar area. 

I am here during lunch at weekends for their lunch special. They have some good selection for their sushi. I got their Atom Bome and Caterpillar. I forgot the last roll I got. The lunch special is about 70% cheaper than their regular price. However, the pieces also cut to 6 pieces instead of 8 pieces. As a result is not much of saving. Why they need a lunch special then. Might as well said lunch reduce pieces. 

Service is good. But I think I always feel be watch during eating. Sushi is just average. Sauce is a bit too much. As a result, they are rated at average.

This Mexican restaurant has inside and outside seating. The outside seating area is to accommodate the customers who smoke or with dog. The bar area is at inside serve extensive drink menu with TV. You can enjoy a gameplay there at football season.

I got the Steak Monterrey. This is skirt steak marinated with and grilled. It accompanied with rice and stuff poblano pepper top with habanero pesto sauce. The stuffing is with shrimp, mushrooms, onion over melted cheese. The stuffing is actually my favorite. However, the main item skirt steak is very tough just to cut. It take me a good 3 minutes to chew a small piece. Meat quality is not that good. It the meat quality improved, this restaurant has potential. 

There is plenty server on the floor. You always can get their attention. Service is good. Not sure about the drink. Seem like each waiter prepared their drink order which tell me no set bartender.

Bar Louie is more open connecting to outdoor. But I do not like darker corner when you seat inside. This bar is second stop on our progressive happy hour tour. 

We started with fried calamari. The calamari is a bit tasteless because the coating is not interesting. May be make more floppy and spice with be more attractive. The second item is the chicken quesadilla. This is more interesting. But still this two item are not attractive enough in compare to nearby happy hour restaurant. However I do like the martini. Their signature martini during the happy hour is very good. I have the Diva martini. I like that one. 

I think the drink is better than the food. They really need to work on the food to attract more customers during happy hour.

About 3.5 stars. We visited at 5:30 Friday, the line has not build up yet. We were able to get a table inside. There is not much of service. The person who take order is a bit slow. He just sit at register for taking order but still slow. The kitchen crew are more alert. They got your order and fried the chicken immediately. 

The Nashville style chicken is using wet batter coating systems. Most of the fried chicken place use dry powder battering then fried immediately. This place have coating mixed with spice and wet it with water. The chicken then dip into the wet coating and fried. This system is more challenging. The Chinese fried chicken is like this system. Why they are 3.5 stars is because the coating getting compact and concentrated. Which mean the oil is old and repetitive fried. The fresh oil or change the oil so often will make the chicken better coating. 

One best thing is the seasoning and the Nashville hot is very well receptive. This is not like Asian hot that numb you mouth and could not taste the food. The hot is acceptable by many Americans. You still can taste the hot heat and the food in the right amount of chili. This I would give them an "A". Price is about most fried chicken place. But I do like their fried and the pickle. It was good.

It is very interesting bar near the Indian Rock Beach. The day we have visited was the the day of bar crawl. I saw many patrons dressed like pirates. It interesting day see some great makeup. 

With Yelp check in, there is complimentary onion ring with beer batter coating. We have order peel shrimp, fried calamari, and grilled haddock. The fried calamari coating is fluffy and good. Is was good enough size to share. The peel shrimp was broil with seasoning. Shrimp is fresh and bouncy. The haddock is just average. It grilled with seasoning on top. I rather it no seasoning. The fish is just ok. I had better elsewhere. 

I biggest concern is we can see the food sit on the counter for Good 5 minutes and no one bring it to us. Until we make known to waitress, she has compensated with free dessert. The dessert is the highlight of the evening. We have the sunshine cake with orange flavor. It was wonderful. The restaurant chef skill is just average. Can be improved.

I think this Thai food has potential. It is at good location. The thing need to improve is the wok technique. Other than that, the interior decoration, furniture and service is measured up to 4 stars. 

We started with squid Tom yum soup. Their Tom yum is lean to sweet side instead of sour. The soup is good. We order the Siam Noodle. This is their house special sauce with shrimp and chicken stir fry rice noodle. I think they are just average if this is a house dish. Not attractive. 

We also order a drunken noodle. We order Thai hot but it is not measured up the heat. The noodle not even burn the edge show this stir fry is not quite high heat with oil. Basically they need improvement. If the cuisine can improve, they will be good Thai here in compare to Bay Area Thai food.

The wing place is rather new in the Temple Terrace. Their wings is about $0.70 per wing which is considered very affordable in the area in comparison to wing place around that area. Their wing choice includes dry rub and tossed sauce with flavor.  

Although the wing is good price but they are tiny on some of them. Not much complaint about it because they charge you less. 

I got the dry rub Parmesan garlic, dry rub Cajun, tossed sauce mangonero. Total of 20 pieces for $14.95. It is football season, wings are essential. The tossed sauce I can live without it. The dry rub is a bit better. The dry rub is not the actual rub on the wing. It is dry sauce tossed with the wing. I like Parmesan garlic better than the Cajun. If they actually dry rub and oven will be better. 

With the competition around their area is tough for them. They some good wing around the area. They need to do something about the process of the wing and how to cook it.

This restaurant has high ratings. Consider one of the popular in the area. During lunch time, the restaurant is pack. They are not too far from Highway I-275, as a result I stop here for lunch. 

I got the traditional dish. I got the Bandeja Paisa. It typical Columbian dish with samples of all cooking. The dish includes grilled steak, sausage, chicharron (fried pork belly with skin), sunny side up egg, arepa, rice and bean, avocado, and sweet plantain. This is to show case the entire cuisine. 

Why three stars. The steak not even close to warm. The sausage is powdery. The egg yolk over cook. It is not liquidity. The best of the dish is the chicharron.  It is crispy and good. 

The service is great. It is not bad at all for the price of the dish $13.50. The service is good. If the cooking can improve, they can be easily 4 stars.

It is an interesting Lao's grocery store. I was hope to get some cook food deli like it show on the store front. Seem like the deli did not operate. We enjoy our shopping there. We pick up few item we have not seen before. 

We got crispy fish chip. Interesting looking. They do have meat department. You can get all pig intestines, stomach or kidney in this store. The store also have some homemade dessert you can pick up. The veggies section is small but sufficient. A lot of frozen seafood. 

Overall this market is small. We like some item we have not try before. Good experience.

This is the first gas station exit for I-275 northbound after Sunshine Skyway. If you need gas after the long bridge, this is the place. Price is reasonable by considering this is at the southern part of the Pinellas County. You may guess they can charge arm and leg but they did not. 

The total have twelve pump. Enough to handle the surge of demand. It is easy to get in and out here. It also has plenty of space to maneuver your car around their parking lot. Security cameras is pointing to the direction of the pump which makes this place safe.

Tung- Tung is one of the few Chinese restaurant that do deliver. The food is average but the deliver is very convenient. We work late in night and few hungry this is a good restaurant to call. They are few restaurants in Temple Terrace answer a call for delivery. 

Many of my friend order veggies or chicken fried rice. Mostly American Chinese food. I actually go for true Chinese food. I got the beef chow fun. It got the sauce and correct wok heat to make it delicious. However some of the noodle has not separated on about 5 % of it. However, they are still good. The beef is flavorful but not tender enough. 

Overall they are still good. If we have the delivery again, I will still order the same thing.

Very close other big oriental supermarket. Some of my friend like this place due to great price and good amount of veggies. Thankfully they open during pandemic. They do control amount of people can enter the store to avoid crowded situations. 

The store have only basic oriental items. Definitely is local favorite. Not for me who are out of town people. It has item I need. I would said it is good carry on the butcher section for type of meat you want.

If you craving for sweet corn arepa, this may be a good place. This Venezuelan place serve variety of dishes. They have a appetizer with variety of taste call Carrusel Siete Estrellas. It has Arepitas Dulces, Cachapas, Pastelitos Andidos. If you don't what it is, I am not going to tell. Go try it and let me know :)

We start with mini Cachapas that a sweet corn arepa top with Venezuelan cheese. Mm good. I like the chewing the cheese. 

Our main menu is bistec la plancha. Is grilled skirt steak with sweet plantain and yuca. The side dish of plantain and yuca is delicious but the steak do not stand out. 

The restaurant has TV to entertain the guess. Seating is ok and acceptable comfort. I would said this is been there done that restaurant. Since the restaurant is to next door kid playground specialty store, a lot parent come to here and eat after taking their kid for fun time.

This is the second PDQ that I have visited. It still good on People Dedicated to Quality. The place is clean and neat. The food is still good but not as good as the first one I have been to.

We got BBQ bacon and Hawaiian chicken sandwich.  The Hawaiian is still good. The BBQ just average. It is a bit too sticky. The Hawaiian chicken is still the best.

The side order of zucchini fries was to soggy. It can be better with extra cost for the combo meal. Other than that, everything is good.

Tara is not allowed dine in during pandemic. But the take out is available. The store open to customers who want generous on the quantity portion. 

I got the the stew Oxtail. This dish come with one side of choices and rice. I have the cabbage as side. The oxtail is stew in high pressure to separate from the bone. Number oxtail given was three big pieces and one small piece. The rice was given generously so you will have full stomach. Great for dinner portions. 

Overall experience is at average. Food is ok. Definitely is budget place in compare to many restaurants.

Dominican restaurant that provide a lot vibe and economic dinning for the local. Many people are here for a meal in saving price. We are here to try out the food for the first time.

The restaurant has the two choices for the food. You can pickup by cafeteria already cook or from the menu. We have order two dishes from the cafeteria and one from the menu. The first dish is a soup with tripe, pig feet, and veggie. Most people only cook tripe soup by it own. It is good twist with the pig feet. Good soup. 

The second dish is a tomato base whole fish. It look awesome but it not my liking taste. Fish meat is too loose. The third dish is a cook up dish of grill steak with onion. I can hear they pound the steak at the kitchen. I like my steak grilled with no sauce. But Dominican steak has sauce on top but a bit salty. 

The food is average. If I choose Latin food, I would go with Cuban style bistec. Service is cafeteria style.

Kwality is try to fusion. There certain things they do well and other things did not carry the load. I would said their dessert is interesting. I have not try their hot food yet, cannot comment on that area. Their store have a huge space. Basically you can buy the food there and eat there. The plenty of table. 

Their curry veggie pastry is one of the good one to try. Enough curry spice and fluffy pastry crush. The dessert is one of the better one. It is by weight. We got several one with colorful display. Some of them are very interesting. We also got their juice as sugar cane. However this is a let down. They give you a small cup and expensive in dollar. I can get better quantity with double of the amount they have offer in Tampa Bay Area. 

Overall is a specialty food center. You can get a hot plate with good price. But for juice, is a bit expensive.

La Hacienda is popular among the local. The plaza parking lot always pack. Most car come to this restaurant. Parking is rime here. We were here at 2 pm. The place still pack. We were lucky to get a table. People who behind us have to wait. 

The food is good. I have Paisa Bandeja Hacienda with upgrades steak. This dish has steak, chicharon, blood sausage, regular sausage, rice, egg, plantains, bean soup. A lot to offer. The chicharron is a little tough to bite de to the skin is or crispy. Like rubber. This can improve by changing the frying oil and keep it crispy. The rest item is a little above average. My wife love her dish. She has Filete de Pescado al Ajillo. The Ajillo sauce is great. I would highly recommend this dish. It is one of the kind. 

The reason they are 3 star is the wait for the food is too long. We waited almost 40 minutes. No wonder the restaurant always pack because everyone is waiting for their food. The chicharron is a typical dish which they must master before anything else. I hope my next visit they can improve on that. They have bakery section. To me is just ok. Bit my wife like it.

It is just ok for the BBQ. This place is kind of new at Brandon area. The store front was decorated with Christmas item when I was visiting there. The draw some new paint on the windows showing the Santa clauses and Mrs Clause. 

We got the sampler platter. It got Saint Louis rib, pull pork, brisket, quarter chicken and two sides. The chicken meat is too powdery. The pull pork is too dry. Only the brisket measure up to the standard. The rib is average. May be is off day for them. It is not up to par.

Jade symbol high end gem in oriental culture. This restaurant start with the name with Jade is meaning for high society dinning for Vietnamese food. We try out this restaurant since many of our friends have checking in at this restaurant. 

We went there for our dinner and we are going to try the non pho items. We have order the grilled short rib and the caramelized pork belly. This two dish certainly look very good when they present to us. Look can be sometime deceiving us. The taste of the short is just so so. It does cook right but not best flavor. The pork belly is a bit tough on skin to bite. But the caramelized does a good job. It have good flavor. 

There is no fireworks on the food. There is mix feeling on their food. I just wonder we hit the off night of the chef. One dish material preparation is off and the other with the seasoning is off. The service is good. It has potential to be good on other items but not the night we have visit.

Drive through is sloooooow. It take 3.5 minutes to move a car. If you cannot wait, just walk in to the counter is faster. I figure if you see more than 5 cars ahead of you, just walk in. This store clerk need to process a bit faster. 

Food is good, just service is slow. I believe they can improve on this front. This store now receive a face lift. It was remodel to modern look. It should a new face resolution for this store

They take my order but have to wait for 3.5 minutes. The cooking process also need to speed up. I hope they can improve since they have new look.

We have invited a family to try this new Filipino restaurant and we all excited. We reach there at Saturday 6:15 and we are the only second group of the customer. Later it filled up with another 6 table before we left the restaurant. They are not that busy. They also advertise you can watch the Floyd Mayweather and Manny Pacquiao 5/2/2015 fight there. Manny Pacquiao is Pilipino super lightweight boxer. 

The waitress is kind to explain to us each dish and what materials are used.  We have started two appetizers. The chicken wing with adobo glaze and the chicken sisig lettuce wrap. We like the chicken sisig. I think if they add some sweet sauce, it will make this dish more attractive. The chicken wing is fried. They are nicely fried plainly. Then it adds the adobo glaze sauce. The chicken wing batter before fried can be adding some spice to enhance the flavor. 

The dishes are beef toscilog, Crispy pata kare kare, mixed grill. The beef toscilog come with half cook egg that you can break the egg yolk and mix with the rice. The pan grill beef make this dish desirable. The crispy pata is the fried pig feet. The pig feet are the lower part of the leg. I prefer upper part which has more meat. The pig feet are fried and I like the other sauce instead of kare kare sauce. 

The mixed grill is the squid, pork belly, chicken and eggplant. Among them I like the grilled eggplant. This is the most expansive dish in the menu $32. Three of us stomach did not receive the food well for this dish. We believe the squid is not the fresh material that causes this. 

Base on Filipino food, the price is at the high side. Quality of material is not the best such as the squid. Service is slow and checks back frequently. Restaurant is well decorated. I think it is worth for a try and been there done that type of deal.

Just average. Food can be exciting but I think it is seasoning. It has enough spice but just not above the typical Greek fast food chain. I like the open seating after order. They bring the food to the table that make it easy. 

I have the grill tilapia sandwich. The size of the fish is big. The blacken spice is not strong enough. The dill sauce has too much lemon with combination of caper. I would rather the caramelize the onion with caper that go well with the fish. Seem like the combination do not for into mixed flavor of the fish. 

We also has the hummus with half pita fried and half non fried. I like this better. Overall the experience is good. Good interior decoration, service is nice and friendly. Taste of the food may need to rediscover through R&D to get a good hold of consumers preferred style.

They are busy consider in USF area for pawn shop. I would consider this place if you need somethings use and not cost a lot of money. We were here for a music instruments amps. However they don't have any. 

The whole store has a lot of large speaker. A lot of use tools a If you have a housing project like lawn care, side pressure wash, power tool. They have them all. The bicycle is a bit old. 

They even have a use boat for sales. I forgot to ask them do they list sale for the consignment item. Overall, they are the biggest store here. The item is a bit old, other than that they are good store.

Sarge is very close the University of Tampa. They are in the food court sharing with three other restaurants. With their location close to the university, they got a lot of college student visits. 

We got the smokehouse club. The meat do pile up like mountain. This sandwich has the pork, chicken and brisket. It top with bacon strips and the claw slaw. The bacon is not quite crispy. Meat is a bit dry. The sandwich can better if they improve on it. Price is matching the amount of food was given.

This restaurant is like Philippino cuisine with upscale dining. This restaurant located at clubhouse of the tennis club. It is surrounded by 17 tennis court. Mainly serving the people who play tennis here. It is kind of tuck away from main street. 

The restaurant is well set up. Restaurant name is Match Point Grilled. It also call Karma coffee. I was confused at first when I walk into the restaurant. We ordered Kare Kare. This dish serve with traditional oxtail. It come with rice. The quantity of oxtail is less and not matching the price listed. The other dish we have is the Beef Afritada. It is tomato base stew. This dish give a little more beef. It is come with rice. 

We feel the price list are not measure up the food that serve. Food is a bit less of the taste. Service is good. Atmosphere is great. It is kind been there done that restaurant.

This is the Italian restaurant that we have try to walk in and we were turn away due to full reservation. But our second visit with reservation was seat immediately. I would highly recommend reservation for this restaurant. I saw many table at least has a bottle of wine. I also read some of the previous review, they allow bring alcohol without open cork fees. 

We have a dish of the seafood linguini with wine sauce and a special of the day with stuff calamari e polenta. The linguini seafood wine sauce can feel a lot of wine in the sauce. However, my wife feel the seafood is a bit bad to her stomach and I also think the sauce is blend. The calamari with red sauce is excellent. I am not the fan of the crab stuffing but love the sauce and calamari. 

It is mix feeling with the experience. It can be 3.5 stars easy. But not for tonight. Service is good but the kitchen need help to put the food out.

May be the dish I have order didn't impress me. I have book mark this place for some time. I was having a high hope for it. Tuk Tuk is rickshaw in Thailand. So this is mobile food.  

The menu show interesting selection. One thing catch my eyes is their crab fried rice. I got one of that. I also got their Thai ice tea. The Thai ice tea has strong enough tea in it. I like it the milk and tea mixed. 

I have the crab fried in Thai hot. It does bring on the heat. But the dish did not impress me for several reasons. The rice is too watery. The tomato put in there actually damp the wetness of the dish. It is not a good combo. The crab meat it spread in thin pieces. It can be chunky. It has crab taste but not really crab meat taste. May be they use the blue crab instead of dungeons. 

Services is average. The initial contact is a bit slow but the close up and paid is quick.

This is for the review strictly about the Poke. Obviously this market located 1 mile away from St Petersburg downtown. This restaurant is located at the neighborhood of Old Southeast, as a result, they call themselves the same name. 

The grocery store's alcohol wine collection has a lot of choices. They do have a wall of soft drink and special drinks in the refrigerator. In the grocery store it has a few seat for anyone who wants to eat there.  

For the poke, since they are situated on the non compete area, it becomes the local favorite. In compare to Tampa Bay Area, they are in the middle of the pack. This is due to competition store has unlimited choices in compare to three choices on the added on. The other place can mixed and match on the sauce. This place has pre set sauce with your choice to add into poke. I have to give them credit some of the sauce are home mixed that other place do not has it. Overall the quantity is just at average in compare other. Add on is so so not quit interesting.

Winn Dixie located convenient location near USF. Many students and local has shop this place. The grocery store is the anchor store of this plaza. It brings a lot of customers to visit. During the pandemic, shoppers wear mask to shop. I wish all grocery store to provide the disposable glove. This way they can touch the item and reshelf if they decide don't want it. 

We visited close 10 before 5pm. But the hot daily already empty their selection. It is too early. I wonder they changed their store hour. Recently the are has a lot of looting. The item on the shelf is medium stock or reshelf. I feel their store is a bit let down. Beer section is a bit high price. The wine selection is average. 

Other than that, the grocery store serve the local need.

Very new restaurant. I decided to try them on. The restaurant seating is about a little challenge. Inside the restaurant mostly high top except a few is normal level table. If you want to sit at normal level, you may want to choose the outside patio seating. Obviously they try to imitate the beer hall type atmosphere with high top seats but it will be challenging for lady with dress. 

This restaurant is open about a month. They still did not get the kink out. The food wait is about 35 minutes. Waiting staff afraid to approach you since you are waiting for the food. We got the habanero wings and the short rib. The wing is actually Buffalo wing with honey ranch type dipping sauce. I am not impressed due to 8 wings for $11 and is just regular buffalo wing. I expect more for the price paid $1.5 a wing with tax. The name not measure up. 

The short rib is a fan. I like it when they braised it or slow temperature long hour grilled. The out side was crispy and nice. This short rib top with sweet mushrooms sauce with cabbage and place over pancakes. This is a great dish. 

Overall the service need to improve, the food waiting time need to cut down, may be grilled the wing with honey after the buffalo sauce was applied will make this wing worth $1.5 a piece. Happy hour half price weekday 2-7 is a plus.

This restaurant is a Thai restaurant that serve sushi. This restaurant locate near my office. This is a place if I have run for the next meeting after the lunch hour. At night time, live jazz music is performed here. 

Today I have the garlic pepper squid and a cup if the tom yum soup. I always order Thai hot. It is really spicy - sweaty hot spicy. You have to be able to tolerance for hot food is you order Thai hot. I am use to it. To most American, the Thai restaurant medium hot mean very hot, mild mean ok hot. The tom yum soup have ingredient of scallop, shrimp, and squid. The tom yum style soup have the tamarind spice with sour and salty taste. It is perfect, for most people just order the regular so you can enjoy and taste the soup. If not it will be too hot. 

The garlic pepper squid is a stir fry dish. The chef need to prepare the garlic sauce with high wok heat to create the burn of oil and the garlic to create the burn taste. This restaurant is ok on this skill. However, overburn create charcoal taste which you don't want. It is a battle of the risk of the chef not to under cook it or burn it. 

I have sushi here before, I can said that I am not a fan of it.

It is about 3.5 stars. A few things can be improved. Overall is a good restaurant. It is food truck standard in a building with control temperature. Chef has good skill. 

I got the two meat large bowl with steak and chicken combo. The steak is the New York Strip meat. But it is thin slice meat. The bowl is bed with rice. The meat is cook over grilled with Korean BBQ sauce. I have added sunny side up egg. I also got spicy pork to go. I eat half over the restaurant and bring home other half. The food do not sit in my stomach well. I have to go to bathroom. I believe is the egg because I finished the egg in the restaurant. When I eat the remaining, it was good. 

If I am there, I will go for the Bibimbap. Cafeteria style. Not much of service. I would prefer the steak to be dice than thin slice.

The nowait online is good to put your wait list before arrive to the restaurant. It definitely a good help to know when your table is ready. Even with nowait check in. They also loss our reservation. Fortunately they back check it when we were there and give us next available. 

The restaurant is busy because they are the most affordable in Hyde Park. Many teenagers who live nearby are hang out at this place. This restaurant look like old dinner. It has the sixty look. You almost can feel the swing dance party is happen any time. 

The food is average compare to many dinner. I guess that have so many customer due to their affordability. We have order the grilled grouper and Goody goody cheese burger pox. The burger is just average. The grouper is good size but they are pan grilled not flame grilled. The fry come with is soggy. This is not a good fry. I believe the fired oil was not change over time and make the French fry soggy. 

Service is not there. Our waiter was missing for good period of time for our close up. Not sure is worth for the visit. However, been there done there.

It is vey small farmer market. It has some art and craft, food, service, clothing and specialty. It located at Centennial Park of Ybor City. It is at the corner of 9th Avenue and 19th St. Parking is easy along the street side. They have parking lot with the fees apply. 

In the park they are some shaded area with roof cover. This area have a lot vendors and pleasant to walk. Across the street is Ybor City Museum State Park which make this Saturday Market a one stop visit. Among the vendors I like the vendor who sell the indoor plants. This indoor plant has multi color and easy to take care. Just a few spray and close the glass enclosure, the steam form on the glass and create natural indoor steam room. 

There are some clothing, buttons vendors. It was very interesting. Some vendor sell gluten free cake. Not many vendor but have something to offer for everyone.

The seafood is fresh here. There are plenty of traffic and people visited this place. We were there 7:30 pm and it was pack. There are many people call in. The phone ring is almost not off the hook. Good thing they have parking around the building. Tables and chairs are provided inside and court yard. There is heavy seafood smell in the building. If you don't like the smell, you can sit outside. 

The seafood here is good price. Catfish or Basa fillet are $4.99 a lbs. they also offer fried seafood platter. We ordered the seafood platter include shrimp, scallops and clam. It is good deal with the entire box fill up till it hard to close the lid. The platter also includes fries and hush puppies. The seafood was fried with batter coating. For my experience, the coating is too thick and no added spice. It is kind of plain. You will need drink to go with the seafood. The positive of the platter is the shrimps are in good size. 

This is a local favorite and many has visit. The food come out quick.

This restaurant use to be a different Vietnamese restaurant. The interior did not change. The traffic for the patron is good here at 5 pm. At least I see 5 table occupied. 

I got the Hu Tieu. It is a seafood Hu Tieu. It has the squid, shrimp, fish ball, shrimp ball. This dish cost $7.50 for small. I have ask them to add the fish cake also. They have charge me extras $2. It is a 25 % mark up. It is a bit steep. The noodle is good and the seafood is fresh. I think the soup is a bit let down due to lack of flavor and the enhanced of fried onions and fried pork fat.  If they can stir fried the pork fat ant onion before adding the soup, it will enhance the taste. 

Overall is good. Services is average. Nothing to boast about. It is been there done that deal. Pinellas Park has too many good Vietnamese food. It will be a good competition.

Interesting decorations and furniture for interior set up. I would said this is a people hang out place. I saw people play with their iPad or smart phone there. However, it did not give me a feeling of great atmosphere. 

They do have two choices of adult only ice cream. I mean not in the film X rated movie. If you think about that is all you...haha. The adult only is alcohol content ice cream. You need to show the ID before you order. My ID is the grey hair :). I have ordered the pumpkin spice rumchata. The alcohol is actually from the rum.  I would said it is tasty. 

The price is a bit in the high side. If I come back, I would try the porky delight and some of the menu items. They located approximately 2.7 miles from the exit of the I-75 and SR 60. Easy to find.

For the Hillsborough county library I been to, this is my least impressive library. It has all the components of library. Book are correctly arrange. 

They have kid section with computer equipment. As usual, you can get free dvd for home entertainment. This library have low ceiling to conserve the cooling bill good for the tax payer.

I was eyes on this restaurant for long time. Every time I pass by there is a long line. Finally a weekday that has no much customers. I was able to walk in and order without waiting. I have it to go. 

I order a palabok fiesta with one non spicy chicken joy. The palabok is rice clear noodle with shrimp, ground pork and egg. It is just an ok dish. The fried chicken joy is better. I also has the spaghetti with two spicy chicken joy. The spicy of the seasoning is actually skin deep. Spaghetti is average. The best among all is peach mango pie. This is their best dish. I would recommend this. 

The order was prepared fast. I really don't like the packaging. It is paper box that is not secure. Especially the food is more heavy than the box can bear. This will be their set back and easy to spill when they not secure properly in the plastic bag with two three order.

My experience is base on the price they charge and the pasta available that day. That day they run out of many things, only two type of pasta available. We got pasta with meat sauce. The process is simple. The only advantage of this restaurant is make the fresh pasta. 

The food is come with paper containers with pasta. Sometime can be messy to reach the last pasta at the bottom. Overall the taste is jus average. I don't see much advantages other than convenience. Price is high for the dish.

This is a 3.5 stars restaurant. It is not yet 4 stars. In compare to many Korean restaurants in Bay Area, I would said they have the most competitive price for their food. Although they are not cheap but is about a dollar to 2 dollars lower different in the Bay Area. 

We have three dishes tonight. We start with Galbi the Korean grilled short rib. The dish is $23 with about 11 pieces of short rib. It was great marinated sauce to the bone. The second dish is the Eemyoonsoo the fried Atlanta Mackerel with lightly salted. This is a whole fish. The size is medium for $17. The edge and top was fried to crispy and crunch. A very good dish to go with beer or rice wine. The last dish is Dolsot Bibimbob. The rice serve in stone bowl. That make the rice burn to crispy at the stone touch edge. This dis has egg, veggies, beef. But I think it is less flavor. They need to work on this dish. 

They are better than most Korean restaurants in Tampa. You still need to wait for the food for a while but the wait time is shorter than the Korean restaurants in Tampa. I still say they need to work on the speed to deliver the food to table. Don't let the customers wait too long. Service is typically as bad as most Korean restaurants.

New Culver with new building, new location, and new market. This will be a challenge to many culver store. It does bring easy comfort food to the area and next to the mall. I have been to 4 culver, it will be comparison among them. 

We are here for buy one get one free ice cream. The coupon is sweet. I have the flavor of the day. It keeps changing every time we're here. The only comment I have is the ice cream melt very fast compared to other location of culver.

Cool name to start the sandwich store. Very systematic to select the sandwich that you want. First identified the name. Then the sandwich of your choice, next type bread, then sauce, last is ingredients include veggies. 

I would said this sandwich store is in the middle of the pack. Because they are systematically layout, they are not flexible to change for their meat selection. For instance if I want just capicola ham only, I will not be able to buy that. I have to select the entire Italian cut including pepperoni, salami. The reason they give is each portion is precut and assembled. You will not be able to twist and change. If I want extra meat, you have to paid entire assembly. 

The sandwich is good taste for Italian, the balsamic sauce is great. But I feel sandwich assembly is thin not wide enough. A meal combo is above $10. It is above medium price range.

Happy hour time with friends in this location. We meet up after work to celebrate. Certainly this Winghouse is the hottest location in Bay Area. 

Tonight is a special night gathering. While we wait for all the friends, I have order a bluemoon. They do not carry Coppertail. Bluemoon is good and cold. We brought a cake to celebrate and the waitress is nice to but it out for us. I have order a smoke BBQ grill wing and two pork chop. The chop is a bit over cook and dry. The chef do not have skill to seal the juice. It accompanied with broccoli and mushrooms gravy with mash potatoes. Food did not impress me. 

The more need to be improved in this winghouse. Table need to be clean, food need to improve and the parking need to be available.

I am excited to try this restaurant. I like to try this hype restaurant with $$$$ for sometime. I hope for top dollar with very good experience. You have a choice to valet for $5 when you are arriving or looking for empty parking in the lot. 

We were planning to try the happy hour before our show in the performance art center. After we have sit down, the hostess tell us the happy hour item is at the bar area or lounge. But they let us sit at the dinning room for happy happy hour item. We have waited them to bring the menu. Later the waiter has come to ask us again then we wait again. We could have gone to lunge area and be done with it. 

We have ordered the lamb lollipop, lobster roll, and the charbroiled oyster. The lamb come in three big pieces with good quantity. The oyster is only three pieces a bit less. The lobster roll I have better elsewhere. The taste did not wow me. 

The ending to pay the bill is quick no wait. I was expecting a lot from this restaurant but did not get the value we paid. Good restaurant but they can be great.

Food is ok. Selection of menu is very little. Fine restaurant at dinner serve with paper napkin for the price we paid is not upscale. Server is friendly. The price do not include dinner roll or bread. No much salad selection. Very limited. 

There should be a lot to offer if they charging a lot of money. Not good with family but good for couple.

I am disappointed for price paid and there is no table cloth service. We were surprised that there is no espresso available after meal. I was more surprise when the waiter refer us to the near by coffee shop if we need the espresso. The rule of restaurant usually don't refer the customer to other food franchise or location.

Tonight drop a star. Food is good but service is below average. Before I order, I have mentioned we have a concert to catch and need the service and food in hurry. We order a nibble before the concert. We sit on the bar also for this reason to get in and out quick. 

I have ordered the Mesquite Grill Oyster Rockefeller. The food come out in 10 minutes. Which is good. But when we close out the bill, the bar tender is dragging the feet. We ask the check and he acknowledged it but he keep circle around get the thing for other customers. Seem like he forget. 

I would said the are few things need to improved. The speed of serving, no hesitation on looking a sit for customers, veggie on the table need to be cover.

When get to this Mall visit, it was second mall of the day. I was still full since we have two restaurant run before it. May be it is time to get something sweet and wait for my wife shopping. You Say When Yogurt Shoppe is the best choice for my sweet run of the night. 

I did not go for the Yogurt because their smoothies is calling my name. The first is to choose type of healthy drink you want then is the flavor. I have chosen the mango banana smoothie. The smoothie is thick. The flavor is average. Even it is a small size but the sixteen ounce is good enough for me to last my wait. 

This shop has yogurt with at least seven flavor for your choice. May be next time I will get the Yogurt. The service is good. The wait is short because it is almost closing hour.

In a Taiwan, there are many tea places with boba or specialty drink. However this place is unique due to the substitution of boba to fruit. 

We were attracting by the picture some of the yelper posted for the drink with fruit. When we arrive, we notice they have yogurt by ounces and big list of specialty drink. We have tasted some of the yogurt and they are in good flavor. For specialty drinks they are break into six categories - fresh brew organic drink, fruit tea, ice milk tea, fruit smoothie, frappe, and hot latte. I am in the fruit drink and going for the Tutti Fruti - green tea with fruits. The tea is very sweet. The nice thing is the chop the fruit with dice size so you can suck through the straw. 

The second drink we have is the mango strawberry smoothie. The smoothie has the chop up fruit. Personally, I prefer boba over fruit. 

The preparation of the drink takes too long. They need to speed up. Overall, it is good experience.

The BBQ place located in a rough neighborhood. If you want find a good food and don't mind the place, this can be your adventure. King BBQ just off Armenia and I-275. There no place to sit. It is a to go place. 

You may not experience the full menu. It is what they are cooking at that day. Today they just have the regular rib and the chicken. The price is good for the meat you get. I got half slab regular ribs for $13. It fill the entire box. The middle low part of the rib was grilled to crispy and not burn. It is very tasty. They do have the BBQ sauce selection with mild, mixed or hot. I have them put the sauce on the side. Since this is full size rib not baby back, the half slab look big.  

The BBQ store is walk in and the grille just in front of you. You can see what you order. They will chop it for you for easy bite.

Nice set up for the store front. I also notice they also have the food truck. They post the location they running their food at the face book page. If you want to track them, please go to their face book page. Tonight their food truck is running to tampa general hospital. 

The set up of the business is order on the counter and they will bring out the food. This a mix of cafeteria style and table service. They do have different source at the counter. If you like add spicy to your food, they have banana hot source and other kind source. As a food crazier, I like their banana hot source. 

It is good place for lunch and dinner. Their lunch and dinner is the same price and they are very reasonable. We have lumpia, sisig, tocsilog, and mango turon. Three courses dinner run $32 for two. That is sweet. The food came with no vegetable attached is the only down site. The y may be can improve on this area by balance the nutrition of the meal by adding some stir fried vege. Their sisig and tocsilog are mainly meat dish with rice. The restaurant mainly serve the pork dish. Their food is close to philipino street food.

I want some snack after the exercise. It is also the football Monday night. So I decided something quick with wings. I think Kentucky fried chicken may be a good choice. 

Recently they have the $10 bucket with a choice of fried chicken, popcorn chicken or wings. I have selected the wings. The drive through is easy since there was no one in front of me. I got my order in two minutes. Nothing better than that. 

The wings are fried correctly. Occasionally the have thick crust. The wings is a bit small compared to many wing place. I have 12 wings for $10 and with tax is about $0.90 per wing. It is average cost. In compared to I have Dry Rub wing for $0.80. I would said this is a three stars.

This is Vietnamese fast food in the mall. This is first of it kind. It you have to choose a mall fast food, I would go for the pho which is more healthy and easy. They are located next to the carousel in the mall. 

They have quite a selection for the type of pho you like. It include the seafood or fish ball noodle soup. I have the meat ball and slice rare beef noodle soup. Soup is good. They may not be the best in the Bay Area but it is good enough for the mall.

They also carry different type of boba smoothie. I did not try their boba but my neighbor boba look very good. 

The service is good. The sale person very patient explained to me each item. The only down side is each item is prepared in package. I like to mix and match which will make thing more interesting.

I am in agree with CoreLife healthy living food. It is a good concept to start the restaurant. This restaurant is wide open seating. One good thing to sell their food is to have many special drinks. These drinks have all you can drink. They are many choices which includes apple green tea I like. Some of the tea is with honey and some with no sugar. Non caffeinated is the fruit punch. 

For the entree I got the grass fed steak plate and tuna poke rice bowl. The steak is grilled there and keep warm in the oven. I do not like the steak medium well. I rather they cook to order since they have some one there to grilled the steak all time. The poke is just average. One good thing is their side. They have purple rice that I like. Other than that, the rest of protein seasoning is average. 

This is order from counter and bring your food to table. Not much of service. Some table still can see cup ring left by previous customer.

I would said this is the best Philippino restaurant in the Bay Area. It is a mix with grocery store and the restaurant. I can see the problem of this restaurant is the response time to the customer. We sit down for 10 minutes before anyone come to ask what I need. In fact, there was no one out at the front for good 10 minutes. We help ourself for the menu. 

We got our orders immediately once we have someone come to our table. The food came out very quick. We order the Binagoongang Baboy - pork with shrimp paste. It you are not use to shrimp paste do not try this dish. I like this dish since the pork are well braise and soft. If they cook this dish with hot chili, it will be much better. 

Our second dish is the most popular dish of the restaurant. It is Da-Long-Tocilog combo. It is a breakfast dish that serve all day. It has fried pickle fish, cure pork meat, pork sausage serve with garlic fried rice and fried egg. This is a very good dish. 

The food is 4 stars, but the service and attentive of the store front is 2.5 stars. So 3 stars for the restaurant. Do I come back. Yes, for the combo breakfast dish that was not serve else where. It has better menu compare to the Bay Area Philippino food restaurants.

John Pass Village offer tourists attraction for the vacationer to visit. The boardwalk offer nice evening stroll. The fishing boat come back with their catch. The fish clean is one of the major attraction when the fishermen with the skill knife fillet the fish. While they cut off the un wanted section, the remain was through into the Bay. There was a lot of pelican waiting to collect the remain and cut off section of the fish. 

A long the boardwalk, many restaurant was there. You can book the fishing trip here. Or you can get the dolphin watch. You also can rent the wave runner. 

The bad side- the high parking fee discourages the local to visit. Why we waste tax money for making this place good but it charges you a lot on parking. The restaurant also did not make a good deal of it. Because of the tourist spot, their price is normally high. As a result, the village has narrow to only tourist.

The restaurant service is good. The server paid good attention to our table. She also have knowledge of the menu and daily special. The restaurant is at prime location at the mall entrance. They got very good customer base. The restaurant is 80% pack in the early dinner hour. 

We got two items from happy hour, we have the oysters and the medium neck clam. Both dishes was fresh and delicious. My wife have fish and chips. The fish is in good large piece. It also has crispy coating. It is good dish with the fries. I have the crab cake. I think the crab cake is below average. I think it has too much dough than crab meat. It do come with string beans and rice. The side dish is a choice from menu. 

Overall experience is good. It is about 3.5 stars. I still think if their menu can be re-engineering with attractive dish in use seasoning, cook method, or flavor, they will do very well.

My first take of the pub is great gathering place in Tampa Palm area. Generally it has good seating area. Most chair is high top. May be a bit difficult for the ladies with dress. This pub not populated with TV. It can be more but enough for each corner. 

This pub food and drink price a generally a dollar more than the other pub. The wings after tax is about $1.3x per wing. Average wing price at USF and New tampa is about $1.00. As a result, we expect to be spectacular. I have blacken wing. The wing is fried correctly. The blackened spice is not so. I think can be improved. I wonder if they have grilled stove. If they do the grilled will add flavor into it. That can be improved easily. 

I like new business because they really bring value to the community. In the same time, they need to be reasonable. I know they invest a lot in a business. So far they have the customers and it is time to correct.

I would give them a fair average restaurant. With that said, they did a good job during pandemic period. They put napkin dispenser for you get a piece napkin to open the door without contact. The food are paid online and no touching in the store to exchange payment. Food is put on the table as barrier from kitchen. Base on your order and name you can pickup your order. 

I order the broccoli beef, Kung Pao chicken, mushroom chicken, fried rice, noodle. The broccoli beef I barely see the beef. I do got a lot of the broccoli. The Kung Pao chicken is better. At least 50 to 50 meat and veggies. The mushroom chicken meat is less veggies is more. All dish has a lot of sauce. Which mean the chef wok a little less and has a lot of water sauce. 

Overall experience is good. The online order need to be pick up in the store instead of drive throu

Great establishment for the new restaurant. Food is very affordable here and better value than any fast food chain. It does bring a lot option for the local residents if you want some things to go and eat it elsewhere. This restaurant provides the Vietnamese cuisine option. I would have many take out from here if I decided not to cook. 

We were here to have the grilled chicken rice bowl and vermicelli grilled beef. I like the food is easy assembly's and fast delivery. I did not try the bah mi yet. Base on their grilled meat technique. The chicken is nice and juicy. The beef marinated a bit light. All meat marinated into the deeper side of the meat. The serving temperature is warm not steaming hot. This is the area may be they need to work on. I like the fried spring roll. It is about 3.5 stars restaurant.

His bakery cafe and sandwich store is local favorite. We were in the area and try something for my book mark. The interesting item will be the the Tomato pie. But we did not go for it. 

We have the carrot cake. The cake is moist and good. I would said they have good dessert. It includes the banana cream pie, red velvet cake and more. There are some good sandwiches post by other including the Cuban sandwich. May be you want to try it. 

Overall is I good. I would call it average.

Basically is a take out restaurant with computer order. There were a few tables to sit. No restroom facilities, only bottles water. It is designed for take out. Menu easy to read. Very simple. 

We got the beef kimbap. This is like sushi roll with bulgogi beef. It has, egg, pickle veggies. Consider this is a large roll. We also got the spicy pork lunch box. It has fried pork dumplings, kimchi, rice and spicy pork. Food is good to have. For take out, they are good. For dine in probably need to consider the situation.

The cinema has a lot slot for single movie. It make convenient for the time of arrival. If you miss one, there is another slot not too far away. The selection seat on half of the cinemas. The other half is just first come first serve. The selection seat is alway nicer with recliner seat with foot rest. Mostly for the newest movie. 

I got the black panther for the night. Since this is mew movie. It has seat selection with recliner. Love the movie. Like the seat. Enjoy my time.  It has 20 cinemas that multiple movie choices. It locate in the mall easy for your teenage kid to watch the movie while you shopping.

I think they have not smooth out the kink of the cafe yet. I will give them a few week before you go again. This review do not reflect the kink that they try to smooth out. It is for their product, service and ambience. 

Ding tea has small and regular size. Their small size really small. I would go for the regular size. The tea has little flavor. Not strong at all. The flavor not stand out. I have the brown sugar monster with milk tea. The brown sugar is just ok. Boba is regular not the the brown sugar boba. My wife have the Hokkaido Coffee. 

You can choose the less ice, medium ice, or more ice. You also can have no ice. They also allow you to adjust the sugar level. This may be the only plus.

We have a group visited at night. The food is set menu. We were exiting to come and enjoy. But my current experience will knock one star off my previous visit. I have order a crushed blackberry agave margarita it take long time to prepare. May be the waiter did not paid attention. I like the drink but the wait is too long. 

I like the appetizers such as crispy calamari, spicy crispy shrimp and crab spinach artichoke dip. But the main entree and dessert disappointing. The entree I have is the shrimp and crab meat linguine. The shrimp is not bouncy enough. My friend has the sea bass. He like it. One of my friend doesn't go for the seafood because the set menu mainly farm raise fish. If he can get it from order menu may be better. 

My dessert is ok but my friend dessert as carrot cake is not as good as he told me.

It is about 3.5 stars restaurant. Being at downtown Tampa, it should be busy.  We were there at Friday around 11:30, this place only 35% fill. These should be easy for them to serve us. By the time we walk out at 12:15 pm. The place is full. 

The lunch special is attractive. I saw the chicken chimichurri hash at lunch special menu is attractive. The dish serve in skillet with potatoes hash, grilled chicken, grilled onion and top with two egg of your choice. Sunny side up is definitely the best to break the egg yolk for the mixed of the hash. This dish also has the chimichurri sauce make this dish decorative. 

For the energy, I have morning meditation drink. It is orange, lemon, turmeric, ginger, agave nectar, and beet. What a drink and nice presentation. 

Service is a little let down at the end.  Food is good.

It was great that I revisit the restaurant since we have a bad experience in the first time. A lot of things have been changed. We were here after late night movie. 

A lot of improvement has been made. Food come out a lot faster. The noodle was prepared correctly not glue together. I have order the devil spicy ramen. It is spicy not super spicy. The soup is still salty. The egg need a bit work - over cook. The noodle need some sesame oil to make flavor better. 

Overall is good. It is big improvement.

This is about 2.5 stars restaurant locate in downtown Tampa. It is about American style Chinese food. Since the quantity and quality that provide on the food served, I round up to 3 stars since we are not able to give half stars. 

If you craving for this type of the Chinese food. This may be your place. Price is at the medium. The food is similar to take out place Chinese food. But they have few house special dish. I was going to try their smoke duck. However, they didn't carry this dish that night. So we change our selection to lobster and shrimp dish and happy family dish. The lobster is deep fried to crispy and the shrimp is cook with hibachi sauce. It is almost like two dish in one combination. Lobster is fresh and so do the shrimp. The happy family is combination of the ingredients with shrimp, scallops, chicken and beef. Within that dish, the beef is the best. 

I cannot tell the about the service since there is only two tables of customers. Chef skill and use of spice need big improvement. Ingredients are good.

It is a fast food joint. Order and paid at counter. Nothing fancy. Just like mall food. Except more personal touch with cooking after order. Seem like fried rice and noodle being pre-cook for assembly. 

I hope for Bento to be here at Bay Area and now they are here which has not impress me. The best thing about this place is their bento box with many items and reasonable price. I would come back lack of time to eat but not for date night. 

We got the Korean beef and the Katsu bento box. The Korean beef did not fare well. But the katsu is good. The string beans has no salt in the bento box. We also got the spicy tuna small with 4 pieces. This item is a bit expensive. However, it has good flavor. 

We got the boba tea which is fun to have. Something I don't understand is when you paid and order at counter, the alway have a tip box to check for 18% to 20%. The only service is bring the food on table. That always doesn't make sense for cafeteria type food service industry.

Late night or late dinner, this is the place open late. Dead Bob has a character for the bars. The price is insanely good for the food. I would said this a good place for gathering. The only thing I don't like is they don't have draft beer. The place is open air. So if some smoke outside, you can smell that. 

We got big wave beer, lobster roll and honey glazed salmon for total of $20. The lobster roll is not the true lobster. The flavor is just ok. But for $8, it is acceptable. The honey glazed salmon is a lot better. The salmon was grilled crispy at both side of the fillet. The honey glazed is good. 

The beer here can bargain if you buy the bucket. This is the best deal. Tuesday has special on big wave beer. The service is a bit let down. But you alway could wave down the person walk by to grab what you need. The bar is lively with a lot of TV for games night.

This holiday inn is at the center of the town. Very convenient. 15 minutes to downtown, 10 minutes to the loop, 25 minutes to Chesterfield Outlet. It is fare in price. 

The facility need some up grade. The hallway definitely need some major renovation. Elevator is working. Parking garage is good and save. Out door parking is available. They do charge your parking. Not much. Less than $4 a day. 

The room is good size. But the bathroom is tiny. Taking a shower is difficult to manipulate around the shower head. This is the area really need improvement. May be glass door instead of shower curtain. 

It is walking distance to the Cathedral and the forest park. Very close to airport and The famous The Loop neighborhood for food and restaurant. Close to university of Washington.

I passed by this restaurant due to my assignments near this location. As a result I got some takeout for my lunch. Their menu is very simple. I ordered the takeout through the phone. However the lady didn't understand what I want. They put on make up the item I want with shrimp as a protein. As a result I got my protein as chickens and pork. 

I order two dishes, the first dish is drunken noodle with Thai hot. I feel that the noodles a little bit wet. They could cook it a little bit longer and dried noodles and make it a little burn the edge. The second dish is Yum beef. This dish is a little bit better, you have a flavor that I need for the salads with a beef.

The pick ups is on terms as what they promise me 15 minute to deliver. There was no way on the pick up. Overall the food is average. Quantity is good.

We know about this restaurant is because of their Taiwanese food. The outside look like Chinese fast food, but they serve Taiwanese cuisine also. If you want to order Taiwanese or the true Chinese food, you need to ask for the Chinese menu. Unfortunately this menu is in Chinese. So bring a friend can read the menu with you for your first adventure. 

The day we were there they have a lot of the ingredients are unavailable. There some dish in the Chinese menu is not available due to missing ingredients. We have ordered the beef braise noodle soup, spicy stir fry chicken, and the spicy beef tendon. I like the most is the spicy chicken. This chicken cook it high BTU cook top. As a result it has burn oil taste that I like. The beef noodles soup still need some work. May be braise a bit longer. The soup base may be changed to bone base soup will be a lot better. 

This is husband and wife service team restaurant. It has local who actually support this restaurant that like their food. The local support is important to keep the business running.

Mi Bandera has been in my bookmark for sometime been want to try it. This was the second Columbian restaurant of the week. They definitely a solid 3 stars and above average. 

Typical Columbian restaurant. I always like Columbian candy they give at the bill. Each restaurant has different candy so do this restaurant. We have the tripe soup, black sausage, churrasco Bandeja paisa. The tripe soup is ok. The churrasco is good flavor, the pork belly do not has salt, the sausage is average, it does give a good portion of food for good price. My wife want to try the black sausage which is blood sausage. It can be better with correct seasoning. 

Our experience here is good. Nothing stand out but solid. The server know a bit English and enough to take your order. Even change the TV channel for you. Overall many Latin people eat there. Many have look at us and curious what we have order. They were surprised we know our order :)

We were here for the weeknight sushi special. They have $1 nigiri, $2 sushi and $3 dollar roll. This are good price. Once you add it together, you may spend up to $17 per person. However, you can try a lot of sushi and roll. 

The experience is a mix. Some roll are good and some just average. I will not complain since the cost per roll is good pricing during weeknight happy hour. They run the special from 5 to 7 pm. Our waitress is super nice. She got our order in quickly at 6:10 pm when we sit down. We were able to get our second order after 30 minutes of eating. The waitress is very courteous to ask us if we like to get the third order 5 minutes before happy hours end.  

They are some room can be improved for the happy hours sushi. The sushi rice flavor can be a bit tasty with correct mixing with sushi rice preparation. The fish meat can be a bit better quality. I have to complement their service is above the scale.

Ha ya- karate chop. No it just the tea. It has some kick in it. No hand chop:) 

Kung fu mean martial art in Chinese. When they use together with food mean their specialty food. I have been to this place 4 times and gather my conclusion of this place. The tea place is upscale. Nice sofa and seat. They have the regular tea mix. You can add toppings of your choice that is when they get you with up charge. The have good enough tea taste. Other than that. They have a lot of toppings or inclusion selection. 

I have the pina colada with mango jelly. Not bad at all. We were here 35 minutes before it closed and we drink to the last minute. This will be the eat around 4th stops. We enjoy our moment with friend here.

This is restaurant is about almost 4 stars. We were here for the friend celebration. I like the decorations inside the restaurant. Something unique and stand out. I like the big round light bulb with low intensity fuel. The bar has the decorations of veggies leaf which is stand out. 

Food certainly has some good choice of seafood selection with seared, ceviche, deep fried and more. Our group of eight has share a lot of food on table. We start with table side guacamole. I would is  good fresh guacamole. Other apps include Guajillo Pork Belly, Plantain Empanadas, traditional snapper ceviche, ahi tuna ceviche, and special salad. I like the tuna and pork belly. 

My main course is the Carne Asada. Steak was cook perfectly but small portion. But the chimichurri is at sour side compare to typical one. I like the accompanying arugula salad with bacon and fruit. We also to taste the fried whole snapper and the shrimp. 

Overall the service is average good. I don't mind to be tag on large group mandatory tip. But 20% is a bit steep. Normally is 18%. Which mean you have not say if the service is bad. A half star deduction here.

Neighborhood Taco Bell for drink and snack. I have never use their food for meal. But I do like their select item over Mc Donald for snack. 

I here mainly for the happiest hour soft drink. During 2pm to 5pm each day, the drink is a dollar. I usually get the Baja blast freeze. They do have other choice like the pomegranate water, other flavor of freeze. Taco Bell generally is healthy choice than Mc Donald in the fast food chain. I remember an old futuristic movie "Demolition Man" shows the only surviving franchise in the future is Taco Bell. The movie shows the people with healthy living and change society and the Taco Bell is the high class restaurant. Imagine that is all we eat in the future???

I also like their snack for the crunchy taco or the steak quesadilla. Love the steak quesadilla here. If they can only using just the Swiss cheese, I will know at their door often.

The Domina's pizza is actually located inside the gas station. I am not much a pizza lover, but if I have to chose the pizza chain domina is my choice. I like old thick crust pizza, I am not a fan of tin crust. If you have to pig out, please go all out with no reservation. At that point you have blown the calories count any how. 

Tonight they have the $5 two topping deal large pizza. It is enough for me and my wife. We have order the pepperoni and bacon. I call in 10 minutes before my pickup and they are ready on time. The two topping deal only on the carry out. Please make a trip to nearby pizza place. The total come to $6. Great value. 

They lay the pepperoni then the bacon on top. The pepperoni is great and crispy. With bacon on top the juice of bacon further cook the pepperoni to give extra crispy. The bacon is great in this sense. Everything go well with bacon. 

Please catch the deal while they last.

I was so look forward to try Blake Crab Cake. I like lump crab meat. Especially they serve Maryland style crab cake. The store is small compared to many restaurant. It is almost like take out. The list of the item was written at the board. I would said this will one of the unique store serve this type of cuisine. 

We got the crab cake and the blue crab fingers claw. The crab cake is deep fry with flour. It does not look like lump crab look that the business picture. As a result, I think is a step down. When the flour and crab meat fried together is not the same just the crab lump meat alone. It will be different. The blue crab claw is delicious. But I think instead of old bay seasoning, the blacken claw is better. 

The experience is just make the mark. Nothing fancy. Portion is a bit small. 5 oz crab cake for $12 is at the high side.

After second visit. This restaurant is about average not just for Malaysian standards but also Asian food standards. We come here second time to determine  how many stars need to be. I have to agree with Mark and Brian for three stars. 

This visit we have order the Beef Rendang, Hainanese Chicken, and Char Quey Teow. Below are the reasons they are average. The beef rendang is at right spice. However they are very mild in spice. They are not spicy. But if you request a spicy beef. They should be able to tone up or down on the spiciness of food by add additional step to prepare in the kitchen. This option was not available. The Hainanese Chicken suppose to be broil and chill in cold water with same process for many time to get the tenderness. But I think just broil once. 

The Char Quey Teow should be dry out stir fry wok cooking. One positive note. All food has the Malaysian taste. It has good spice.

3.5 stars restaurant to my book. This new Rice Bean has been building their new hop for long time. Finally it opened for business. It does bring crowd in from the area. There are not much good mom and pop restaurant in the area to compete. They are really located at good spot for business. 

We got the Churrasco and Bistec Empanado. The churrasco is the skirt steak. Their skirt steak cut like a strip with about 1" diameter and 7" long. I prefer to thin and at Falda cut which they don't carry. The marinated sauce is good. The steak is cook to medium not like my order medium rare. Overall is a good dish. The Bistec Empanado is breaded thin steak. The breaded coating has no taste. I have been many Latin restaurant have better coating than them. 

One other thing. We walk into the restaurant and there was no line on Tuesday night. The hostess still saying we have to wait for ten minutes for table. I see there is open table. At the end we choose the bar instead of waiting. Service is not attentive. Many area of the restaurant need to improve. Service, hostess, food.

I like our food here but not necessary we have best time. First the wait, the hostess tell us 10-15 minutes. It turn up another ten minutes. I walk around and found empty tables but they are not occupied by anyone. I went to check when is our turn, they lead me to the same empty table that I found 5 minutes ago. The seat is just below the AC vent. I can feel the drip of the water. They definitely need to check this vent on their off hour. Make sure water molecules is contained. 

The only thing I like about this place is the service on the table and the food. Which is the most important. My wife has the Thai Coconut-Lime Chicken. It a bit lime heavy at the end. The best is the Hibachi Steak. It is the hunger steak with shiitake mushrooms in slice, caramel onion and sprout. It also included the wasabi mash potatoes and tempura asparagus. This steak is cook with the ginger sauce which is a good match. 

Service is good over the dining time. Food come out the right time compare to my last visit. I would said the hostess need to paid attention to the empty table. Customers is less patient when exceed to the wait acknowledge time. The AC vent need to be clean and make not dripping water. Who know what dust has the water has collected.

Japanese food or good can be found in this store. Essential items also can be found here. This store is not big but have enough items for your need. Many packaging food is available. 

The store owner is very friendly. She welcomes you with a warm smile. The ceramic section include bowl or tea set is nicely presented. 

It also carry some munchies section. Porky is widely sold in the store. It do have some frozen section.

Columbian restaurant that open not long ago. It was on the neighborhood paper. Decided to give them a try. At the front of the store, they display the Latin pastry and finger food and chicharon. It was beautifully displayed. We got some of their pastry. The pastry is definitely 5 stars item. I would love to buy their pastry again. Pastry are delicious. Love it. 

For the entrees, we have the Carne A la Plancha. It single grilled steak. The other dish is the grilled skirt steak. I would said they are not the expert of the steak. The control of the steak temperature or marinated sauce is not there. The technique is average. 

Service is good. Food come out quick. The table and seating is basic set in the restaurant. They have a few booth you can have more privacy.

Fast food in restaurant setting. 

The restaurant is big with a lot of seating. When it was just open, it is almost like the attraction of the Brandon. It has nice deco in the interior. It still busy even now. Now is not like pack crazy. 

I am just wants to get the experience of it. We have the fried halibut, grilled tuna sandwich and chocolate cake. The halibut do not impress me. It is a small sandwich compare to Burger King or McDonald fish sandwich. The grilled tuna is excellent with taste. The chocolate cake that day is not moist but it has the softness and good mix of cake. 

Overall, they are average. They do have a lot help on kitchen. However, the food still take 10 minutes. Compare to many fast food, they are considered slow to deliver.

No many Krispy Kreme left in Tampa Bay Area. Definitely not many hot now doughnuts store. I love hot now sign because it is just make it. The doughnut is fresh out from kitchen. The Dough is still warm and the sugar glaze just harden. Krispy Kreme offer that in their doughnut store. 

I am here for their special coupon for a dozen glaze donuts for $5. Only the email sign up user have that coupon. It is good deal. I got the hot now freshly made donuts. It was so yummy and I have to open my box and eat them immediately. It definitely allows me to go for second donut after I have finished the first one. 

This location is my first visit. I think the wait can be shortened since there is not many customers during 3 pm.

This sandwich is a historic sandwich store. Many my friends gave god review here. As a result, I have bookmarked this place 4 years ago. I am happy to be here. 

I have the Cuban sandwich. It was great the sandwich was prepared very fast. I do ask the sandwich to be toasted. After first bite, I think the whole sandwich is sour compared to most of the Cuban sandwich I have. I think the pickle was put there with the pickle sauce was dip into it. The sandwich did not has the mojo pork. Not sure which version of Cuban sandwich is this. I would is Americano sandwich not Cuban.

Hugh Flea Market. They charge $1 parking fees on top of collecting rent from each vendor. Not sure this will work properly. But they do get a lot of foot traffic each day. The entire market may need 2 hour to finish. They have variety. There are restroom stop at certain location. 

The section includes the non cover area and cover area. The cover area has the good court. Many of the vendors from food court run by Asian. It has Vietnamese pho to American Breakfast. 

The vendor include Wendy Closet which I think a great place to buy cloth for roll play. We got two blinker magnet cloth pin in the market. 

The outside vendor has the farmers market. We got a box of mango with eight mango for great price. I do like to walk undercover. This is great for a sunny day.

I was here Thursday night. The place have good crowd considering it located in community plaza. The bar area is empty and since I am eating a lone, might as well have the bar and watch football game. 

They have the free lime margarita with purchased a meal. So I go for the free margaritas. Unfortunately they don't have margaritas. Since when a Mexican restaurant doesn't serve margaritas. May be only the food truck. 

I got the seafood fajitas. Seem like the picture in yelp show this dish very intriguing. It has scallops, shrimp, mussels, crab meat and fish. This is the first time I have fajitas with crab meat. Very interesting. I actually like this dish. I like the seafood over caramelized onion. The taste is good. I like the fried bean and rice come with it. Except the salsa is too little. Food is 4 Stars. 

The service is average. Waiters are arguing who to help. It will be ok for the common good. Food come out quick enough. The chip on the pre-meal smell like fried in the old oil pot.

The Tampa Bay has an explosion on the poke restaurant. This poke is kind of close to town and country area. I like that most of the restaurant spread out the Tampa Bay Area. I like the building has high ceilings but. 

Here you can have their preset menu with ingredients and sauce arranged or build your own. I got my base as sushi rice. I also got all ingredients except onion and edamame. I also added an add on seaweed salad dressing addition scoop of protein. It turn the add on and tax is close $15. It is at high side for poke. A assembly food is a bit high. 

I would they are in the middle of the pack for poke. Reason below. Many place offer multi scoop proteins. Many of the added on is part of the deal with no additional cost. Some other place even mix the sauce, protein and ingredients before putting in the bowl. This extra step will help instead of putting the sauce drizzle on the top.

It is 3.5 stars restaurant. I am here to get the drink after exercise. I like boba so I check the are who has boba. This store is famous on poke. Not sure boba also good or not. I give them a try. I got the coffee slush. The slush is kind of watery. The boba is not the chewy type boba more like the jello. Also the boba has not flavor. One good thing is they have good coffee mixed in it. 

For boba they are average. But I saw customers in front of me got the poke which has good mixed up. It look delicious. May be poke is the only thing to go here

My friend like Green Lemon for Tuesday Taco. I can see this is a hip place due to the atmosphere of the place. Many young people love this because affordable food with booze. 

There are few things that the restaurant is just an average. Number one is wait for table. Number two is wait for the food. Number three is very tire server. Number four is in experience hostess. All this actually give them 2.5 stars. Wait for table is 45 minutes, wait for the food after order is 25 minutes, waitress is beat up and tired. Not sure how many table they have to take care. Hostess tell you 30 to 45 minutes wait is definitely 45 minutes. They need to clean up the table sooner and allow to clear the queue wait line. Since you have to wait for the food, it make wait line longer. 

One thing they can improve dramatically is make sure each order come out quickly which will reduce the wait. It definitely effects the tip because of the wait and cause the waitress look tired and not happy. Kitchen crew definitely need to come out the food more efficient. Mexican food should be easy assembly and able to deliver quickly.

This an average Roll ice cream store. I have better on other places. With that said. I have to give them credit on the only one in New Tampa right now which we don't need to drive too far to have one. 

This is only base in the roll ice cream. They have many item such crepe choco Coro new item and Acai. This items was not reviewed. Base on their roll ice cream, the selection is good. But the toppings is little. The charge is high. 

We have the on snow in the assembly menu. The toppings are chocolate roll cookies and top with coconut flakes. The ice cream is creamy than other roll ice cream. Which is a good thing. I only don't like the pricing and so little toppings. Overall experience is good. I would give them at average among the same business. However, I do want to try their crepe. It look interesting.
