One good thing can said about this experience is the dessert. All other just ok.

It is good deal when you travel just yourself without any luggage. This airline will charge you every thing. Any select seat, luggage, carry on, travel insurance and more. I think they are more gear for short duration travel. If you have a same day business trip, this airline definitely a good deal. 

This big yellow air bus is ok. The plane we took delay 30 minutes. But they did warn us about it. Many has bring their duffle bag or back pack. Just to avoid additional charges. But for a good non stop flight to Chicago is perfect. 

Leg room is just ok. Random seat assignment is free but if you decided to seat close to exit more leg room, you may want to paid extra. The seat is a bit un comfortable due to non reclining seat. In the same time, the padding on the seat is thin. Not good for long hour travel. 

Drink, snack or food is extra. When you paid the luggage service, you think you may get the luggage sooner. It end up we have to wait for 30 minutes. Overall experience is below par. But is I have a short trip, I may considering it.

A converted gas station to restaurant now is popular and hip place in Seminole Height. This restaurant is close to I-275 and easy to get to. Parking is available at the restaurant make it convenient to visit. It is a popular place for brunch and coffee. Night time it turn to gathering beer place. 

I got the Cortado to start for coffee. It is thick espresso. This type of espresso is actually origin from Spain or Portugal. Then we have BBQ pork sandwich. I think their sandwich is average. However, I like their salad that accompanied it. 

So far they have the right ideas for the hip place with garage seating and outside gas station seating. If they can add some gaming material will attract more people. Service is extremely good. Their waiter and waitress are well trained.

I was hype about the visit due to many good reviews. It must be good to visit them with all the good reviews. However our visit turn not to the best or to any tea house standard. 

The outside is hippie look. I am guessing is live free and enjoy. There was many of patrons who are there already. The outside seating is popular due to current good weather. We have chosen the inside since the outside is full. Once enter the AC area, the grilled smell is over the place. It need good ventilation. Your clothes will be cover with food smell even after 2 hours. 

We order the Kiwi Pear tea with sweeten and the Billy Chang sandwich. The sandwich is slice smoke beef brisket with strawberry jelly. We waited over 40 minutes for a sandwich to be cooked. The Kiwi Pear tea is very light in taste. Even the tea is not strong. However, it allows three refills. 

Well, this restaurant is done and done. Been there. Not sure we get a lot out of it.

I was there around 4:30 pm on Sunday. The shelf for the pastry is almost empty. I bought the last guava pastry. The last pastry seem like very oily smell at my first bite. Not bad for the price just a bit over a dollar. The guava taste good. 

This place is famous on their fabulous Cuban bread. It is long mean very long bread. Many come to here just to have that. It is good value. The entire store has no ac and good to raise the yeast.

This restaurant is category at average. It is close to 3.5 stars but not yet there. The restaurant is very close to MD oriental market. It is walking distance to next door. If they lack of any ingredients, very much can get it at oriental market. 

I got the two rolls special. Tuna and fried white fish roll. The roll is not spectacular. Very basic. It does come with a choice of soup and salad. My wife has the Pork ramen. It has good charsiew Pork. It also included the fish cake. The soup base is a bit light. Most of the ramen has good bone base. This soup may need some thing like black sesame oil to enhance the flavor. 

The only thing I like is the Kama. Kama is the grilled yellowtail collar. I like it. It is not best best I have for Kama. But good enough. The service is easy since not many customers.

The visit was pleasant. The restaurant is located in a very nice plaza and they are kind in the center attractions of the plaza. Parking is free but the plaza is a bit busy to share parking among all other businesses. This is a minus for the location for customers to find parking. 

The interior is great pen space. Plenty of light to see what you eating. I likes the system order your food at counter and they bring it to the table. It is convenient for the customers. 

I have ordered the tuna sandwich. I ask if the tuna is seared. And she acknowledged. However, they serve it fried with coating at outward of tuna. It is different than I was ask. Which is good with me. The tuna is just average because they probably fried from frozen. 

I think their counter clerk need to know what they serve if a customer asking about the the food. Overall is good experience.

Brooklyn Water Bagel is 3.5 stars. The yelp review is on target. The 3 to 4 stars is all base on when they take the first bite on to go order. If the customer take the bite there will be close to 4 stars. If it is to go, it may not be the same experience. 

I have the chorizo bagel. For the price is about at the high side. Like the scrabble egg in it. The chorizo is ok. Food is definitely a breakfast style. As a result they close at 3 pm. May be changed a bit here and there will bring them to better product.

Good enough Mall. However the choke point is the entrance of the mall at SR 60. If you are seasoned shopper, you will not like this entrance. The less busy entrance is from the Causeway Blvd. this will be the tip if you want to shop here. Other entrance included the Lee Roy Salmon Expressway. 

Once you are in the mall, it was comfort to walk anywhere. The mall it self is good. If you want to get your morning walk in control environment, it is a good choice. It will take 20 minutes round trip and you do not worry smell, car noises or safety.  

It has multiple anchors store including Sear, Macy, Dillard, Dick Sporting good, JC Penny. Definitely has some bargains since they have been here long. Black Friday is always crazy on the parking. But we were lucky. I am not sure they have security cameras in the parking lot. If you shop a lot and decided to put the purchased items in the car, I would said move your car to next space so the thief will no know and thinking you are leaving already.

We were here to have the celebration of the birthday of a yelp friend. There are unique theme like steam engine, conductor, train depot, tanker car, on the track, boxcar. At least they use this theme in the food menu. 

When we arrived, the 97X radio holding a promotion there and give away the concert ticket. Then there is a promotion from the Tito Vodka to give up shot in the beginning. Then Tito Vodka came over to our table to buy a round of drinks for everyone in the table. Thank you for such a generous gift. 

Back to the restaurant and bar. The food was put in the order and our drink was not deliver for some time. I mean a long time. We realize this place don't have enough help to serve the table. Soon we realize the waitress probably serve the food and help on the kitchen to get our food in order. 

I would said the service is bad but for the situation we saw, cannot blame on this condition. It is the miss management to be blame. I hope they get their act together.

Come here for a drink and checking this place out. Typical bar setup at soho area with one half facing the outside street and the other half facing inside the building. 

We have not try their food. Can said too much about it. However the set up of the bar is nice. The have some selection of the local draft. The beer is in the high side on the happy hour price compare to south Tampa. They do have the foot ball bucket during the game time. They do have good selection of Pinot Noir. 

The only thing I don't like are their complimentary valet parking. If I don't want them to park my car, I cannot park on their lot. I have look for street parking. Sometimes if don't plan and go to this place and you don't want valet, you cannot park there. I do like their service. However, overall cost of drink is a bit higher compare to normal bar.

This is a New Orleans cuisine restaurant. The place fill up quickly at 6:00 pm. If you try to bit the crown, come before 5:30 for Saturday dinning. 

The interior design beautiful. They have beautiful ceiling, and I bet you not many people notice it. They also have a beautiful bar with top rate bourbon on the shelf. The bar is busy when we were there because a lot people waiting for their table. 

Tonight we have the duck confit spring roll as a appetizer. The spring roll have more vege than the duck. Not a fan. The entree are the rabbit dumpling and the bayou bolognese. The rabbit is serve with cast iron braise pot. This technique help the food not to get burn or over cook. The bolognese is actually a wild boar sausage. The both entree is ok not a wild factor. However, the restaurant allow you to select a side such as fried oyster for only addition $7. 

The service is good. I may have to be back to see other dish will give me a wow factor. The self parking is a challenge but the valet is available. This is a restaurant good for family or couple.

In search of taco, i decide to be this place since the other taco place is too busy. This place been in my bookmark for some time. This taco bus is the oldest in the Bay Area among all the taco bus. I thought they must has something special item from other taco bus. They did not. 

They open very late to 4 am in the morning. If you cannot find a place to eat at late hours, this place may be open. A yellow bus is a order center. Then you can take your order number and they will bring the food to you.  

The taco is below average from our current taco fever. They may need to improve since Tampa already has many mobile taco open and better. Meat seasoning need to step up. The meat juicy need to preserve when they serve. Overall, I would say this is a jewel in Tampa to symbolize the Tampa.

Bobacup is getting a bit slagging today. A few week ago I find out after 9 pm they don't cook the Hong Kong waffle and we turn away. Last night they completely remove from the menu. Don't understand it. Their reply is not popular item. 

Now they serve crepes with fruit and whip cream. I have order the one with strawberry and banana. Not my liking. When they roll the crepe and try to pack in the fruit in cone shape. It doesn't work. I would rather they lay it flat fold three folds with the fruit inside. It turn out they give out their best product and go to somethings they are not good at. 

Although the boba menu is still there, but the service with no smile, and the quality is not there. A drop of star from my previous review. I wonder some time what define their identity.

This will be the last restaurant to try during the St. Pete restaurant week. We call ahead today and they indicate no reservation is needed. Their outside sitting is very popular. The inside has plenty of room. 

Our first courses are the ceviche and chicken stay skewers. The satay is the best dish tonight. It herb grilled with chilies sauce and peanut glazed. The ceviche is the mahi mahi in lime juice. It just ok compare to most of Peruvian restaurant. 

To night they don't have duck leg so we order two grilled Cobia fish as second course. The Cobia is grill and top with pineapple salsa and avocado purée. I like the accompanying almond rice. Is is very tasty. 

Our final courses are the cheesecake and the strawberry rhubarb pie. The crust of the pie is perfect. The cheesecake is most and good. 

Overall the service is a bit slow. The reason they have 3 stars is no stand out dish. No wow factor and some seafood chain restaurant is better than them. The menu may need to improve to attract. For the price we paid, they may not be the best choice.

With all the hype, I finally make it to this place with a group of yelp friend. This is the second capital taco that is open other than the original from the Land O Lake. I am fan for the original capital taco.

We arrive one hour before it close. The capital taco has strange hour. They close at 8 pm and it is early to my standards. So far they only open 3 day a week. They are planning to open more than 3 days a week. 

I have order the west coast special with tiger shrimp my favorite at the original capital taco and the Johnny Reb. The shrimp is over cook. It is not bouncy. The Jonny Reb is a bit better. Somehow the food on second capital taco do not measure to their original store. 

Other not positive note is they got this big space. However, the seating is too less. Why they want the customer to take it to go or wait on the table since they can have more table. Since they are in the corner store why not add some out door seating. The line is also long, I would said they can take the order on the line like Chick fillets. 

There are many area they can improve. I hope my next visit they can improve.

This restaurant open not long ago. We have coupon in our mail box as a result we set a day aside to try them out. They are very close to the movie theater and it is a good way to draw the crowd. 

Their Menu is very simple. First choose a starch or veggies. Second select the proteins or type of meat. Third select the toppings then select the sauce. We have order the lamb kabobs with rice with all toppings and the sauce. This is good dish. Our second dish is chicken kabob with hummus. This is a better dish. Each dish is under $10. Dish portion is a bit small. 

Compare to nearby middle eastern and Greek food, they are at the middle of the pack. Please prepare to wait since each order is grilled at the spot. You will need to be patience for this restaurant. They may need to improve they delivery method because the lunch crowd do not have that much of time to eat.

This place is located very remotely. It got the space it need to hold large group. The kitchen and the order center are separated. Every time they take an order they when to back room to prepare it. It leave the front counter empty. 

The smoothie they prepare is a bit in the sweet side. I think may be the juice they have is sweet. Overall the wait is short. I order the pomegranate plunge. It has good taste. Love the nature drink.

I cannot believe I am actually writing a review for Arby's. in all goodness, I do like their new product. The new pork belly sandwich has attracted me to be here. I have pork belly sandwich at BBQ place before. I just want to see how they fare with their new sandwich. It give you 2 slide of thick pork belly, crispy onions, and smoke cheddar cheese. This combination sound very good. The pork belly was cook harmony and it go well with the crispy onions. It create crunchy taste. The sauce is good. As I did not have lunch and have the late lunch everything taste good. 

I was only one at three o'clock drive through. After paying, it still need to wait for 3 minutes to cook. The drive through lane need to be reconstructed in this location. A lot pot holes that cumulate the dirty water. May be make it more desirable for the drive through experience.

In compare to the Oggi in David Island, I think this restaurant is on the average. First thing is about the demographic. The David Island has high average income than the lutz location. Same chicken dish may be able to sell at David Island for $22 a dish may not be affordable in Lutz. In a way this is BBQ countryside. Just chicken as protein may not be able to satisfy the customers come for a restaurant. 

We got chicken Parmesan and Pistachio Chicken Cutlets Palermo Style. The Parmesan chicken is typical Parmesan I can else way for less price. It need to be spectacular for charging over $20. However, the Pistachio chicken is definitely worth the price because not typical restaurant has it. It has good crust and sauce. Very pleasant. 

Service is below average in compare to the David Island store. Not many table is serving, but is a bit difficult to get hold of the waitress. May be this place is biggest and separated by a partition wall between the bar and dinning area. Seem like many waiters congregate on the bar area and not been able to see what happens to the dinning hall.

Great drive through. The wait is good but sometime they have hang out with customer and delay the deliver time for the drive through. I like to get the dollar menu during the happy hour time 2-5 pm. I have the Baja freeze and the spicy chicken crunch. The food is good for afternoon snack.

Try their cinnamon ball. Sweet Cream inside

It must be the local favorite since it is high stars rating. However not work for season visitor like I am. It has good flavor. It is almost like food truck standard. I hope they can improve to restaurant dish. Add more item in the menu for attractive item. 

I have the noodle that recommended by the restaurant. We arrive 8:30 pm and they said if we could finish by 9:00 pm because they are closing. The food came out quick. I would said the food is as the food truck standard even though they serve in the restaurant. I would said some food truck may be has better wok cooking technique than their dish. 

Overall is a good experience. It is about 3.5 stars but they do have a lot of room to improve. Service is good. We finish our food at 8:55 and take the one not finish to go.

I think if the restaurant need to be competitive at International Plaza, they need to restructure their menu, pricing, drink, new dish. This is due to my recent visit and find their food not attractive. In fact, that can be tell from how many customers visited this restaurant. 

We started with their Lobstah Tacos. We got the full menu 3 taco. Most of the meat is from the lobster crawl. I would not recommend use the tip meat at the crawl. They are powdery and not great. They need to mixed with body and crawl meat but remove the tip of the crawl meat. 

Our second dish is seafood poke bowl. Their poke is not attractive at all. With the same price, there are many poke place do better than them. This dish need a lot of improvement. The third dish is the key west crab cake sandwich. This dish is a little better. But I would use fully dungeons crab meat. Mixed other item and become the crab cake is a bit low side to impress the customers. 

Service is good. But I think they have many waiters stand around until the customers notified them.

This new health food supermarket may be the first at northeastern Tampa. Food is not cheap. Basically you need to be their mailing member to save some money. Once you are in their mailing list, you will receive some coupons to compete the price of regular supermarket. 

I like several thing about this supermarket is their select your own quantity on several item. It is by bulk organic and natural food. It includes the grain, flour, bean and more. Base out your need daily and get it fresh. The deli section is just Ok. I know it is healthy food and the preparation on seasoning is light. I like heavy seasoning. 

To regular shoppers who come here once or twice a week may be a bit expensive in compare to other supermarket. But if you everything healthy, is not a bad choice.

There are not many Boston Market Chicken in Tampa. This location may only one in Temple Terrace. I like the one in New Tampa and decided to try it on this location. 

I think the rotisserie chicken may need some work. The marinated spice did not go enough to the bone. It is important to get the marinated spice into the meat. The other things is the chicken need to grilled a bit more to crispy the skin.  It is the crispy and tasty skin that make the name of the Boston Market. One thing they done very well is the maintenance of juicy meat. This may be due to their good technique. 

I have the three pieces dark meat which is good enough for a meal. It come with two sides of your choice. I had the sweet potatoes yum and the mixed sautéed veggies. This is a good choice. Overall my experience is good.

The Greek goddess always have good healthy food. This Acropolis has been here for long time. But I was surprised to see a slow Friday lunch crowd. I have been to this place on weekday and they have more crowd. 

We were early at 11:30 am. I have order blacken salmon salad special of the day and my wife got the grilled chicken wrap. It take more than the normal air time for the food to come out. The salmon was grilled to perfect but the blacken can be better. I like the salad dressing. The potatoes salad on top of the salad is creative. The grilled chicken can improve a bit better by marinated over night to enhance the flavor and add some salt. 

The decorations of the restaurant is contemporary. However, the booth seat need a new leather refurbished. Service is slow.

I always like Popeyes fried chicken. When first landed in this country, the place I went for college is Louisiana. That time I am not use to burger for my oriental taste. But Popeyes fried chicken is well accepted by my taste. Especially those spicy fried chicken.

I got the spicy chicken strip combo with popcorn shrimp. I like them spicy. The chicken strips are very nice and bread coated. The popcorn shrimp is just so so. I went with the combo. My order is close to nine pm. They already not brew any sweet tea. This store is a bit lazy not accommodate the customers need. I have if they have some on the drive through. They also out of sweet tea. 

A southern food cannot provide sweet tea is not quite accommodating. Not wonder the rating is not high. Many of the waitresses know what I need but walk away from my request. I have been to some other Popeyes and they're not like that.

Good gas station at the corner. Cash and credit is same price. 8 pumps total. It has a middle island for convenient store and people who paying cash. It is a simple typical gas station. 8 pump is enough to handle the traffic volume there. 

The drive way is big enough for the circular driveway. Security cameras is mounted to pumps area and store entrance to protect the public. I would not have any problem to pump here at night.

Keegan have been show on food network when Guy featured in one of his episodes. They have some item that Guy want to try. If you visit their restaurants, there is Guy signature poster in the restaurant. 

The famous dishes include blackened grouper sandwich and charbroiled octopus. This two dishes are the best of the restaurants. I have ordered this two dishes to try. The blackened grouper come with mango chutney. The blackened is one of the kind. It is southern style spice. I like that better. The fish is in good portion.

The normal charbroiled octopus is about two tentacles. They give you 4 tentacles. The chargrilled is good but need to perfect it. The marinated spice is perfect but the grill technique need improvement to seal the tentacles juice. 

The services are good. I like food. They have good quantities.

Local restaurant serve Caribbean style food. The setup like a bar restaurant. There were a lot of people during the lunch time for the out side seating and the bar area during weekends lunch time. Seem like business is doing well. 

I come here for the take out order. During lunch, the lunch menu daily special is a bit cheaper than dinner. I got the jerk chicken and the jerk salmon. Both of them have option of two choices of side. I got the coconut rice, black bean, sautéed veggies, mash sweet potatoes. The side was interesting. However the meat seasoning is more into American flavor than the island flavor. This a lot mild to suitable the local people taste. 

The wait for the take out is about 18 minutes after order. They did offer me water while I wait. The responsive of the waiter is on point.

One of the few oriental grocery that open during pandemic. Mainly Vietnamese customers are visiting this store. Most food are also gear for Vietnamese food. The store is kind of strange. It link to jewelry store next door. 

The items are not as complete compare to larger grocery store. But is it convenient for the local to pick up item they need. Aisle is a bit narrow to save space for more good to display. The munchies aisle is limited. I could not find the items I like. 

Selection of item is good enough for you to cook a meal.

I have been to many burger join, the smashburger is the first. I was excited to try out some new burger. They carry burger, chicken, salad and shake. Very simple menu. They have options to order online and they also have options to create your own sandwich. 

I got the Swiss Truffle Mushroom. The burger is juicy and seem like cook with butter. It is definitely moist and great mushroom cream sauce. The charge above $7 a burger. Pricy. The bun and burger is tinny. It is like burger junior. For the price, I may not want this burger. 

The open late till 10 pm. Not many customers during that time. I only have wait 5 minutes for them to cook. The meal is add additional 5 bucks. I decided not to. The whole combo may be difficult to attract customers. But their side is good choice. It include grilled Brussels sprouts.

I would said this restaurant is in the middle of the pack. May be their high star rating is due to the local favorite. The restaurant is located on the corner of the plaza. It also serves sushi. They no longer take yelp 15% off coupon. 

We started with the Tom yum chicken soup. It has some flavor of Thai but not strong enough. Soup a bit salty. We have the chicken satay appetizer. I think this is their best dish. The entree we have pad Thai. I think they can do a better job on this one. The peanut sauce is not a lot. The noodle is ok. We also got the drunken noodle that not in the menu. But I am disappointed for not spicy enough when I have order the Thai hot. Second, they noodle in the wok seem like just a small BTU technique which I can do it at home. If I order this in restaurant, I expect high BTU wok with burn oil cooking. I cannot find it here. The last dish is the duck basil. The duck is filet. The dish is sweet. I would said is a ok dish. 

Overall my experience is average. The dishes are  too Americanize. They need to paid attention to customers requests of how spicy the dish. Chef technique need to improve. I would said is take out quality.

Rubio is a nicely presented new fast food with actually a comfort food of America with Mexican background. Are they true authentic Mexican food, probably not. But I can said it is fusion Mexican food. 

We have order the Coastal Trio and Salsa Verde Shrimp two taco plate. It is order on the counter and the food bring to the table. The grilled fish and shrimp are average. Yes, they show grilled mark but grilled technique should be have smoke flavor or grilled mark burn meat flavor. The fried fish is good. 

The main reason they are average is the food is a big blend. However they have good interior decoration. Place is very clean may be they still new. Salsa is more in liquidity stage instead of chop up process. This tell you fast food process because it is easy to produce liquid than chop up.

Old Navy definitely is the most like by many people. Their clothing are made to American style and widely accepted by general population. Their price of the clothing is affordable that welcome by many consumer. This is one of my wife favorites store just to shop. May be she can find something she like. 

It was always easy for us to visit when we have extra time before the cinema show. They very close to the cinema. It is obvious visit for close proximity. There have their fashion statement to fit the typical people who looking for.

Oh well, this is average among the restaurant over here. Marrow do have some Americans cuisine. However, what I take for this restaurant may not measure to the value you paid while other restaurant may be do better than them. 

We were here to try their food first time. We have the Tavern 'slammin' steak sandwich. With upgrade side to grilled asparagus it is close to $20 dish. I expect this should be smashing dish. It turn out the meat is is just few cold cut on hot bun. I have give them with nice skirt steak. But it is cold cut. The upgrade asparagus only come in 4 strings. 

The second dish is better. The chicken stack. It is grilled. Also about same price I have for steak sandwich. In compare to near by restaurant, I think the nearby restaurant may be better. I know the competition is tough. But I think they can do better. 

Our service is good. Just some time they waitress not paid the highest attention to our table during meal. But when get paid, it was quick.

If you come drink is good. If you come for food, this may not a good choice. World of beer surprise me that they serve food. However, the food come out of the kitchen is too slow. Menu do not have good choices. 

I got one of the special mojito. But I feel the cocktail is too light on the alcohol percentage. The drink feel like soft drink. Unless you go with their draft beer or bottle beer. Other than that, I not recommend their cocktails. 

We order three tacos for snacks, it take 30 minutes to come out. I think this area need big improvement. The shrimp taco save them one stars. If not it is 2.5 stars.

I would said above average restaurant. This is local favorite restaurant which get a high review. The choice of the restaurants are not much in Wesley Chapel. I would said they are one of the better one in this area.

We have the mixed grilled, lamb pita, and the appetizer. The appetizer has some sour material in it to create the appetite. This is a good start. The mixed grilled is decent. Meat may need a bit more heavy seasoning. It can improve the meat by sealing the juice of the meat. 

I saw the price range has went up since other people review not long ago. They have been adjusting their pricing quite often. They are getting with competing with Greek fast food chain may lose this batter since they are in very remote area with less customer traffic. I would said for the current value, they are about 3.5 stars.

This Kung Fu tea is in the middle of the pack. We got the coffee slush with boba and the winter melon milk tea. I agree with Vivian that they need to improve the mixologist of the tea. Somehow it do not have the taste of harmony. The ingredients is good. The honey boba is still very good. But the the tea bitterness need to tone down. Caffeine is well maintained but the the tea bitterness somehow need to reduce. Milk is a bit heavy compare to many milk tea I have tasted. 

This restaurant has token ramen section. We did not try their food this time. But will plan next visit to try their hot food. I like the open kitchen with glass wall allow the customers see their food preparation. It has increased the interest of the food.

Our experience is about two and half stars. Below are some of the reasons why. First. The food did not sit well in the stomach. I have to go to bathroom twice. After almost $70 of food. I expect it to be high quality. Some how it has not meet the standard may be we are the early crow at 5 pm. Second, the soup is part of the all you can eat but the machine is broken, the soup is regular room temperature. I think this should be be prepared and ready all time. Third.
